title: NSF & HDR ML Hackathon
description: Built an autoencoder with a k-means clustering and neural network to identify anomalous gravitational waves in data recorded from the Washington and Lousiana LIGO detectors.

title: Predicting Vermont Business Ratings & Recommending Local Favorites
description: Made models with Ridge Regression & XGBoost to predict Vermont Business Ratings: ultimately XGBoost performed the best. Also built several recommender systems with lightFM, fastFM, and SVD to suggest businesses to users: SVD model performed the best.

title: Jane Street Market Prediction Kaggle Competition
description: Performed exploratory analyses on a dataset with 100+ anonymized features to create a predictve model with XGBoost as for whether a stock (across different time horizons) is worth purchasing

title: Zoning Analysis & Predictive Modeling of Power Outages
description: Developed a predictive model and conducted detailed data analyses on power outages in the U.S. from 2000 to 2016. Particularly, zoning analyses, hypothesis testings, and building a robust model was done to predict the number of customers affected by major outages

title: UCSD Startup: Dormi
description: With support from Dennis White, the CEO of Cytodome and an MBA student at UCSD, I led a group of five others in developing a business model and prototype of a better on-campus housing platform for UCSD

title: UCSD Startup: Recommending Where to Park
description: After forming a group with two others, I initiated contact with UCSD adminsitration to get API access of live parking data. The plan was to build a platform to help UCSD students coordinate thier commute to campus.

title: Animals of the World
description: Made an endangered animal awareness website pulling from APIs to showcase in my high school coding class

title: Club Compass
description: With a group of friends, I designed a social media platform for school clubs to list themselves on, post events, and handle official documentation.

title: Time2Thrift
description: In late 2020, San Diego thrift shops were no longer able to function because of COVID. I figured if I could design an ecommerce website to host several nearby thrift shops and also setup a COVID-friendly pickup/delivery system, I would be helping a good amount of people. I set out on this intiative after assembling a group of acquaintances.
